{"id": 113979, "acmi_id": "183636", "title": "Mad Max Beyond Thunderdome", "title_annotation": "", "slug": "mad-max-beyond-thunderdome", "creator_credit": "George Miller and George Ogilvie", "credit_line": "<p>Courtesy Kennedy Miller Mitchell Films Pty Ltd</p>", "headline_credit": "Australia, 1985", "video_links": [], "record_type": "work", "type": "Film", "is_on_display": true, "last_on_display_place": "ACMI: Gallery 1", "last_on_display_date": "2031-02-16", "is_context_indigenous": false, "material_description": "", "unpublished": false, "external": false, "first_production_date": "1985-01-01T11:00:00+11:00", "commissioned": false, "public_domain": false, "external_references": [], "brief_description": "<p>George Miller&#8217;s Mad Max revolutionised movies when it tore through cinemas in 1979. Bursting with stunning practical effects, explosive set pieces and iconic costumes, the original Mad Max trilogy (1979-85) cemented its place in pop culture before roaring back to life 30 years later.</p>", "constellations_primary": [], "constellations_other": [], "recommendations": [], "title_for_label": "<p>Mad Max Beyond Thunderdome</p>", "creator_credit_for_label": "<p>George Miller and George Ogilvie</p>", "headline_credit_for_label": "<p>Australia, 1985</p>", "description": "<p>Taking an unexpected direction from the genre Miller established with his highly influential previous films, <i>Mad Max: Beyond Thunderdome</i> finds our reluctant hero coming face-to-face with the feudal Aunty Entity (Tina Turner), who lords over Bartertown and the deadly battle arena, Thunderdome.</p>\n<p>Less emphasis on car chases and more on the brutal tribal world Aunty Entity and her minions reign over, the film sees Max leading a band of feral orphans to freedom. Never fear though, <i>Beyond Thunderdome</i> still bristles with mind-boggling retro-fitted cars, hair-raising stunt work, bizarre costumes and intricate world building to make this third entry into the series as white-knuckled as its predecessors.</p>", "description_for_label": ["<p>Taking an unexpected direction from the genre Miller established with his highly influential previous films, <i>Mad Max: Beyond Thunderdome</i> finds our reluctant hero coming face-to-face with the feudal Aunty Entity (Tina Turner), who lords over Bartertown and the deadly battle arena, Thunderdome.</p>\n<p>Less emphasis on car chases and more on the brutal tribal world Aunty Entity and her minions reign over, the film sees Max leading a band of feral orphans to freedom. Never fear though, <i>Beyond Thunderdome</i> still bristles with mind-boggling retro-fitted cars, hair-raising stunt work, bizarre costumes and intricate world building to make this third entry into the series as white-knuckled as its predecessors.</p>"], "credit_line_for_label": "<p>Courtesy Kennedy Miller Mitchell Films Pty Ltd</p>", "details": [{"label": "Curatorial section", "display_values": ["The Story of the Moving Image&nbsp;→ Moving Australia&nbsp;→ MA-03. Car Culture&nbsp;→ MA-03-C01"]}, {"label": "Object Types", "display_values": ["Moving image file/Digital"]}], "stats": {"tap_count": 0}, "links": [{"url": "https://www.justwatch.com/au/movie/mad-max-beyond-thunderdome", "title": "Stream, rent or buy at <span>JustWatch</span>", "source": "justwatch"}], "creators_primary": [{"id": 2685681, "name": "George Miller", "creator_id": 66844, "creator_wikidata_id": "Q446960", "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2685682, "name": "George Ogilvie", "creator_id": 20795, "creator_wikidata_id": "Q3101803", "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "creators_other": [], "media_note": null, "holdings": [], "part_of": null, "parts": [], "part_siblings": [], "group": {"id": 107699, "acmi_id": "", "title": "The Mad Max film series", "title_annotation": "", "slug": "mad-max", "creator_credit": "", "credit_line": "<p>Australia / USA, 1979–2015</p>", "headline_credit": "", "video_links": [], "record_type": "grou